  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_0' aria-label=\" Govindappa Gounder @ Govindasamy (Dead) versus K. Vijayakumar and Ors. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('0','2025','2025_9_1229_1238','2025INSC1134'); ><font size='4'> <strong>GOVINDAPPA GOUNDER @ GOVINDASAMY (DEAD)<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>K. VIJAYAKUMAR AND ORS. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 9 S.C.R. 1229</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 1134</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010008822025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : J.B. PARDIWALA, SANDEEP MEHTA</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Whether there is any cogent material or evidence to indicate that the appellants had indulged in cutting of trees or its branches or digging up the land and thereby causing substantial damage so as to bring the case within the ambit of s.3(2)(b), Tamil Protection Act, 1955. Headnotes&dagger; Tamil Nadu Cultivating Tenants Protection Act, 1955 &ndash; s.3(2)(b) &ndash; Suit filed by the respondents claiming to be the owners of the subject land seeking permanent injunction against the appellants restraining them from cutting trees or from causing<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 10-09-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 7464/2011</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Disposed off</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('0','2025','2025_9_1229_1238','2025INSC1134','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitv